com.mozilla.secops.input

Class InputElement

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.mozilla.secops.input.InputElement
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class InputElement
extends Object
implements Serializable
    InputElement represents a set of input sources that will always result in a single output collection.

      • setConfigurationTicks

        public InputElement setConfigurationTicks(String cfgTickMessage,
                                          Integer cfgTickInterval,
                                          long cfgTickMax)
        Set configuration ticks for input element

        Note that although InputElement is serializable to/from JSON, configuration ticks are specifically excluded from this. If an input element is initialized from JSON and configuration ticks are desired, these must be set manually.

        Parameters:
        cfgTickMessage - JSON message string to use
        cfgTickInterval - Tick interval in seconds
        cfgTickMax - Maximum number of ticks to generate before exiting
        Returns:
        this for chaining
